#: ../../manual/game_engine/physics/types/occluder.rst:6
msgid ""
"If an Occlude type object is between the camera and another object, that "
"other object will not be rasterized (calculated for rendering). It is "
"culled because it is occluded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/physics/types/occluder.rst:10
msgid ""
"There is a demo blend-file to exemplify some concepts: `BGE-Physics-"
"Objects-Occluder.blend <https://wiki.blender.org/wiki/File:BGE-Physics-"
"Objects-Occluder.blend>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/physics/types/occluder.rst:13
msgid "A messed-up, subdivided Cube named \"Cube\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/physics/types/occluder.rst:14
